    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:383
    old "His long fingers tap against the parchment windows of a lantern. Its frame is cheap, made of oak. “‘Tis glued, en ‘tis quiet,” he says while shaking it in the air. “Ne as fancy as the iron ones with oil, but you can carry it in caves without luring all the corpse eaters en goblins. Perfect for a traveler, just take a look.” \n\nInside the lantern you find a place for a candle. Not a great match for people living in wooden houses. “Hide en glue are ne easy to make, but I will ne ask for more than four rings.” \n\nThe last sack is as wide as a saddle and three hands tall. It contains a whole bunch of undyed, linen sheets. \n\n“We usually keep them for traders, but we could use a few dragon rings. And who knows if there’s ever going to be a next caravan?” He gives you a long look. “Interested?” "
    new ""

