    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:3225
    old "“Aye, I keep them in the hall. Smoked mutton, a sack of dried fruits, nuts, biscuits. We eat fresh here, en pay with work. Coins are ne worth much.” When he thinks, his lips move as well. “Let’s say, one ring for enough food to fill you for two days.” \n\nIn {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color}, that kind of price would buy you three, even four times as much food. \n\n“If you’re in a mood for spending, I also have something special, just give me a minute.” He goes upstairs and returns with a small, wooden box and a hand-long leather sheath. “‘Tis a teeth set.” You’re afraid of what he’s going to show you, but when he opens the box, you realize he meant {i}teeth-cleaning{/i}. \n\n“See?” He points at three different compartments. “Salt, cloves, and mint. You mix whatever you want here,” the fourth holds only a small pestle, made of polished stone. “En here are the twigs you need, they’ll last for months.” \n\nSeeing you’re not convinced, he takes a deep breath. “Well, we do ne let outsiders bathe in our Creek, but give me two dragons en I’ll ask my kids to get you in shape. You’ll get a tub with soap en rose oil, en they’ll wash your clothes in water. I’ll cook you something nice, as much as you can eat.” "
