    old "“I do ne know,” he scratches his beard. “There was one vagabond, but he was ne here for long. En did ne do much. A timid fellow. Talks loudly, but is afraid of everything, especially the guards. His face is touched by flames. Has a big {i}ballista{/i},” he says this word with a strange accent, smirking, “en a large bird as his beast of burden. I do ne know what to say.” He shrugs. “He went south, en is most likely gone.” "
