    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:3919
    old "You’re welcomed by {color=#f6d6bd}eight elders{/color} gathered in a semi-circle, watching your steps closely. They’re not as large as {color=#f6d6bd}the workers{/color}, and their clothes are far from humble - instead of hemp pants or tunics, they wear colorful robes and dresses made of wool. They vary in style, length, and embellishment, separating them from the outfits of monks. \n\nYou spot belts and cords, sandals and closed shoes. One person is bald, one has silver hair long enough to cover her back like a cape. Most of {color=#f6d6bd}the druids{/color} are clean and rested, though one is a bit of a sloven, with uncombed hair, stained clothes, and dusty feet. \n\nAlso, unlike priests of {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color}, their hands are marked by scars, hard skin, old burns, and missing fingers. \n\nStill in silence, a woman with a staff steps forwards. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:3929
    old "Her gray robe is decorated with a brown thread that portrays leaves, tree branches, and birds. She’s over fifty, but the youngest one of them all. Her back is straight, the gray hair only an inch long. She doesn’t need a walking stick - her weapon is smooth, longer than she is tall. \n\nHer blue eyes are vigilant and keenly observe your face, as if in search of venom in your nose and lips. Her lips are thin and small, formed into an austere line that shakes slightly, as if she’s on the brink of a burst of anger. \n\nShe says nothing. "
