    old "She’s standing like a statue. “This word means naething to us. A healthy soul cares ne for {i}honor{/i}, for it belongs to humans en their weak thoughts. Honor can ne burn nor suffocate, for ‘tis already as dead as a rock, waiting for a slingshot to throw it.” She opens her eyes and for a moment you see them not as blue, but rather as gray, like an autumn drizzle. \n\nShe takes a step back. “{i}Your{/i} people would see your words as kind, but you are, en will be, an outsider. We’ll listen, but you’ll ne change us.” "
