    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:3976
    old "“What was that?” whispers another druid, maybe from outrage, or maybe from old age. The woman answers before anyone has a chance to repeat your words. \n\n“I’m well aware. Tha’s what makes {i}words{/i} limiting. We try to cross the frozen lakes in boots that are ne our own, on trails that are familiar, yet stupid. We put hope in these old incantations to avoid being asked for our truth.” \n\nThe woman opens her eyes, as cold as ice. “You do ne know our ways. You bring to us only what you understand, en what we fear. Speak your matter, but be careful.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:3991
    old "She closes her eyes and tilts her head forward. You hear the mutter of workers and elders. “What was that?” whispers another druid, maybe from outrage, or maybe from old age. The woman answers before anyone has a chance to repeat your words. \n\n“We share laughter with those we trust, but every muscle in ma shell makes me beware of a wolf. Every change is a threat, en {i}strangers{/i} bring them more than forest fires.” She opens her eyes and for a moment they are shinier, brighter, but also hostile. “{i}Your{/i} people would see your words as kind, but you are, en will be, an outsider. We’ll listen, but you’ll ne change us.” \n\nHer words are slow and careful, as if she’s afraid to drop them. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4003
    old "She closes her eyes and tilts her head to the left. You listen to the creek, the hammer, and to your own breath. \n\n“I do ne know {i}who{/i} you are,” she finally answers. “Nor {i}why{/i} you are. Every muscle in ma shell makes me beware of a wolf, but {i}ma{/i} village believes you defend roads.” She pauses and looks at your clothes and equipment. “Eva though our ancestors were here for centuries, some still think they {i}need{/i} paths, travelers, dragon rings. Your presence here is a new log for the flame of lies.” For a moment her eyes seem shinier, brighter, but also hostile. \n\n“You are, en will be, an outsider. We’ll listen, but you’ll ne change us.” Her words are slow and soft, as if she’s tasting them. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4018
    old "She closes her eyes and raises her chin, “looking” at you through her eyelids. You hear the mutter of workers and elders. “What was that?” whispers another druid, maybe from outrage, or maybe from old age. The woman answers before anyone has a chance to repeat your words. \n\n“Every muscle in ma shell makes me beware of a wolf. Every change is a threat, en {i}strangers{/i} bring them more than forest fires.” She opens her eyes and for a moment they are shinier, brighter, but also hostile. “Ne only you do ne know our ways, eva {i}your{/i} people would see a beast in you. Tamed, touched by humans, en therefore - cruel.” \n\nShe takes a step back and grabs her staff with both hands. “You are, en will be, an outsider. Speak your matter, en begone.” Her words are slow and careful, as if she’s afraid to drop them. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4033
    old "After many long breaths she moves closer, her steps and smile gentle. She smells of fresh thyme, but there’s an unfamiliar hint to it. Her free fingers reach for your chest, but don’t touch it. “Let me see your face, traveler.” \n\nYou straighten up. Her smile is polite and vague, but her eyes, which now seem a bit brighter than they were just a moment ago, are warm. “Your arrival is welcomed by us, eva though the arrival may open the flood of change. Share with us your thoughts, en we’ll share ours with you.” Her words are slow and soft, as if she’s delighted by their taste. "
