    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4183
    old "“Eva the laws of {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color} must be enough to see our way,” she pauses, making a puzzled frown. “‘Tis ne a wild cherry-tree, of which fruit belongs to squirrels, starlings, en drifters. My ancestors were the guardians of its sapling, our blood flows in its branches. The tree is a part of {i}our{/i} village, ne the wilderness.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4206
    old "Her lips form a thin line. “Do ne seek our praise for a sacrifice we did ne wish for.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4230
    old "She grabs her staff with both hands, and disapproving looks surround you. One of the druids puts his hands on his sides, another one whispers into the ear of an old man, while one of the women crosses her arms. \n\n“Your words are a disgrace,” she whispers. “Or a terrible joke.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4255
    old "She looks at you in silence, then lowers her head. “Maybe so, but ne as it is. The one who lives in the southern cave may tell you more, but show him respect. He deserves it more than all of us.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4280
    old "She hits the ground with her staff, making a thud much louder than you’d expect from such a short soul. “Do ne be a thief. We may wish you nae harm, but read your soul. This decision should ne be a cityfolk’s to make.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4297
    old "She reaches out to you, palm up. You give her the fruit, feeling the warm touch of her hand. Her eyes are gentler, like the ocean after a storm. “Soon there will be a poor soul who’s going to gasp for their last breath, en this Seed will give them strength en years, en joy to all of us. You’re doing the right thing.” \n\nThe other druids nod. Their faces are not as grim, and you see a couple of smiles. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4314
    old "When she responds to your brief tale, you can’t tell if her whisper is filled with reprimand, or appreciation. \n\n“It does ne fit me to put one soul above another. ‘Tis true that the mayor pushes the village into a time of struggle, but ne because of bad will. Tha’s what she was taught, en what saves her from her own past. Aye, she pursues power, en aye, the’s weakness in it. I {i}do{/i} think she needs to change, for everyone’s sake. But each one of us struggles to bloom, ne just her.” \n\nHer blue eyes resemble light flower petals. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4328
    old "She turns one of her ears toward you, as if to hear you better. “But you’ve already finished your work with {color=#f6d6bd}Thais{/color}. You ignored our request, en your assistance is nae longer required.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4337
    old "She looks at the nearby workers. Even though they are engaged in their own tasks, she lowers her voice. “En ‘tis a good thing that you came here first.” She spares you a polite nod. “The hamlet should stay as it is. {color=#f6d6bd}Howler’s Dell{/color} needs nae growth.” \n\nHer shoulders relax, as if there’s nothing more to add. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4337
    old "“Tell me more.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4337
    old "“...So it’s just politics. There isn’t even a {i}wild spirit{/i} to be afraid of?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4337
    old "“If you expect me to lie, I need to hear your offer.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4337
    old "I nod and change the topic."
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4355
    old "She looks at the nearby workers. Even though they are engaged in their own tasks, she lowers her voice. “Yet you spoke with {color=#f6d6bd}the mayor{/color} before you came here.” During the long pause, she observes the details of her staff, without blinking. “The hamlet should stay as it is. {color=#f6d6bd}Howler’s Dell{/color} needs nae growth.” \n\nHer shoulders relax, as if there’s nothing more to add. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4375
    old "“Our people need nae more gluttony, nae more opulence. Nae creature can ever gain everything that it dreams of, en tha’s a hurtful pursuit, a run that breaks limbs.” \n\nHer lips get thinner. “{color=#f6d6bd}Thais’{/color} heart belongs to {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color}. Give her what she wants now en she’ll be weakened. When the day of hardship comes, she will ne have enough strength to accept it.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4395
    old "Her eyes shine, lively as lightning. “We do ne {i}trade{/i}, stranger. We do ne beg, do ne bribe, do ne promise. We give what is deserved. We do what needs to be done. If your shell is ne empty, you’ll do what’s {i}right{/i}.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4413
    old "Without a word, she taps on her staff with her fingers. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4435
    old "She smiles gently, then steps back and bows deeply. Seeing this, the nearby druids also lower their heads. \n\n“The others may ne know it yet, but you’ve chosen their safety over their greed. Your kind heart will be remembered.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4447
    old "Her stare makes you think of a frozen pond, cracking from a strike of a lightning. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4473
    old "You tell her what you’ve learned at the village gates, making her lean on her staff, touching it with her cheek. \n\n“We can ne help with this tragedy. The people of {color=#f6d6bd}Old Págos{/color} are ne our friends and we will ne risk our lives for theirs.” \n\nShe turns toward the rest of her gathering. After their nods, she takes a deep breath. As she speaks, she looks at the ground. \n\n[custom1] "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4473
    old "“Thanks. I’ll see what he has to say.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4473
    old "“...Thanks.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4473
    old "I try to hide my annoyance. These druids are both selfish and useless."
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4533
    old "Once you tell her about the island, she puts her left index finger on her lips, thinking. “[howlersdell_elpis_about_asterion_help3][howlersdell_elpis_about_asterion_help1] [howlersdell_elpis_about_asterion_help2]” \n\n“We do ne care for this man, but we see you as our ally, en wish you well. Come en see me before you leave. My soul will heal your wounds en strengthen your shell.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4533
    old "“Thank you. Please, heal me now.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4533
    old "“I’ll come to you later on, when I’ll truly need your powers.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4549
    old "Once you tell her about the island, she puts her left index finger on her lips, thinking. “[howlersdell_elpis_about_asterion_help3][howlersdell_elpis_about_asterion_help1][howlersdell_elpis_about_asterion_help2]” \n\n“We do ne care for this man, en we see you as a stranger. We will ne help you in your journey.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4568
    old "She puts her staff on the ground and gets closer, surrounding you with the scent of fresh thyme. She puts her hands on your waist and stares into your eyes. Time freezes, and you’re locked in a pillar of blue ice, falling to the bottom of a lake, of an ocean of cool air. The waves of pneuma crawl through your skin. \n\nWhen you open your eyes, gasping for air, {color=#f6d6bd}Elpis{/color} is already a few steps away from you, giving you a warm smile. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4579
    old "She grabs her staff with both hands. “The awoken spit onto the order of things, on time en nature. When held by human spells, they only grow, waiting for the pneuma of corruption to cover their bones. Their will is simple, en will never be forgotten. They {i}will{/i} hunt for those we care for, en they {i}will{/i} drink their blood.” Her face hides any emotion, her voice is monotonous, but her fingers are getting pale. “The curse of necromancy does ne enter our gathering.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4590
    old "She looks at the other elders. “I doubt this boy did something that would require the attention of the cityfolk.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4609
    old "She observes you in silence. “I’m ne sure why you would ask about our neighbors,” her voice gets lower with every word, “but you showed us kind gestures before. He’s young, lost, and sad. To heal, he ought to seek a friendly shoulder among his people, ne in the world outside.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4623
    old "She almost drops her staff. Her lips start to shake, betraying her peaceful words. \n\n“He’s one of us. But there were differences between our paths, en he has decided to be on his own. Tha’s his right, en we respect his will.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4635
    old "She steps away, tilting her staff toward the other druids, who look at you gently. “The’s nae master among us. I’ve answers for our neighbors en I know how to guide them, tha’s all. For now, I’m trusted, but I’m ne above anyone, en I take upon maself the burdens of daily life from the shoulders of the elders. One day, ma soul will get cloudier, or eva lost in madness, like ma mother’s before me. Then, ma lips will be sealed en a better shell will take ma place.” \n\nYou can’t tell if her eyes show sadness, or relief. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4645
    old "She tilts her head to the right and looks directly into your eyes. “What do you want to know?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4645
    old "“I’d like to hear your teachings.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4645
    old "“What does it mean to be a druid?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4645
    old "“Wright’s followers have their Tablets. How about you?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4645
    old "“How do you feel about other religions?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4645
    old "“There are many rumors surrounding druids. Some of them portray you as rather cruel.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4666
    old "“Give away what you can, take only what you need. From your soul, from the soil, from the fellowship of humans. You’ll leave behind only ashes. Accept it, en grow in peace.” \n\nShe ends with a kind smile. “If you think ‘tis ne much, you’re right. If you think any soul has enough years to follow this path fully, your soul is already beset by thorns.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4666
    old "(lie) “In my home, our elders taught us the same thing. And I believe they’re right.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4666
    old "“In my home, our elders taught us the same thing. And I believe they’re right.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4666
    old "“It’s not what I’ve been told by my elders, but I understand where you’re coming from.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4666
    old "“For me, Wright’s teachings make more sense.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4695
    old "She nods slowly. “Each place has a different world en a different time. The ways of your ancestors were shaped to serve them, as it is with us.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4716
    old "Her lips get thinner and she moves her staff in front of her, partially covering her face. She looks at you with one shiny eye. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4755
    old "Her voice hits like thunder, making you step away. “Liar. On your neck, you wear the sign of death. How dare you look in my eyes with venom on your tongue?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4766
    old "She raises her left hand and touches your cheek gently. At first, you feel the warmth of her skin, then you lose track of time, as if her blue eyes have thrown you into a deep lake. When you shake this feeling off, you feel refreshed. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4766
    old "“That’s... Not right. You should have asked me first.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4771
    old "She observes you with a modest, kind smile. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4789
    old "She steps back, her eyes wide open. After a few moments, she bows to you. \n\n“I made a mistake.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4815
    old "“To be worthy of trust. Our elders have to {i}trust{/i} that we’ll master our shells under their guidance, en use them to strengthen all of us. Our neighbors have to {i}trust{/i} that we’re worthy of their food, eva if we do ne work with our hands. The creatures need to {i}trust{/i} that we deserve to enter their woods.” \n\nShe observes you for a bit and her fingers tap on her staff. “This trust would never be put in an outsider.[custom1]” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4837
    old "“We do ne have to {i}feel{/i} about them. If they let us live, we will ne strike first. A preacher was here once, when I was but a teen,” her eyes get a bit more cloudy. “I {i}see{/i} that one could take the Tablets and grow upon them. But The Wright burns the freedom of others, en their followers build their gray, dead temples from the skulls of those who do ne listen. {i}We{/i} request trust, ne slavery.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4858
    old "“Nae one ought to seek wisdom in every mouth they see.” Her thin lips form a smirk, but her voice gets stronger. “The butchers of the Unites are driven by fear. Afraid to admit their old malice, to give up on their dreams of power, of comfort. They make us the monsters of their tales, for they want their people to look away as they hunt us. We’re a mirror of their weakness, the sun to their shadow - we’re the proof that they do ne {i}have to{/i} rule.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4879
    old "For a moment you think she’s not sure how to answer, but you then realize that she’s humming to herself silently. She raises her hand and gestures for you to look around. “The world of our ancestors was ne the same as the one we see. They had their truth, we have ours. Stories come from humans. The animals think naething of them, yet prosper.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4904
    old "She looks toward your axe and clamps her hand over her staff with new strength. “We are ne ones to tell our village how to act, or how to think. If they decide to follow {i}their{/i} mayor, we’ll follow.” \n\nShe lowers her voice and her gaze is like a storm. “When a bear enters your house, you do ne scream at it, nor hold the door for it to leave. You wait, or throw it a fish. But if it heads to the bed of your child, you jump on its back, eva if all you have are your teeth.” For a single heartbeat, you see a red line in her eye. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4916
    old "“Ne an easy question. She may live with us as an honorable elder; or be sent into the woods with naething more than the shirt on her back, like a traitor; or be acknowledged as a fair leader with good answers to our doubts.” She rests her head on her staff and gives you a tired look. “Whatever happens, our neighbors will take peace from it, knowing nae one is above judgment.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4928
    old "A few of the elders mutter, and she gives them a grim look, as blue as ancient ice. “I ca ne help you.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4928
    old "(elpis1 set)"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4943
    old "There’s a lightning in her blue eyes, and while the other druids give you suspicious looks, they say nothing. “I wish I could teach you, but the truth is,” she swallows, and you notice a hint of shame in her voice, “I do ne know much about that place. The’s but one forest speaker who carries this old tale, en ‘tis the elder living in the cave in the south. Ask him...” With every word she puts more of her weight on her staff. “To do me a favor, en teach you what I can ne.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4957
    old "She listens to your tale without so much as a frown, and before she utters her first word, the other druids step away. \n\n“His request, if real, would be understandable, but I will ne give away ma neighbors’ possessions to an outsider, especially for nothing in return. I need to know you deserve this type of gesture - either because of ma own trust, or our village’s.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4964
    old "She listens to your tale without so much as a frown, and before she utters her first word, the other druids step away. \n\n“I know where the things you seek are, en ne just the wand. I’m eva willing to give them back.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4964
    old "“But you want something in return.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4974
    old "You catch a hint of shame in her blink. “I {i}ought to{/i} ask for something. I’m under nae obligation to return the possessions of a runaway, but I’m ne too blind to spot the value of a kind gesture. I want you to return it, tha’s all.” \n\n{color=#f6d6bd}Elpis’{/color} whisper isn’t much different from her regular speech. She nods toward {color=#f6d6bd}the tall druid{/color} with the club who used to keep watch by the entrance, and he approaches the workers at the building site. \n\nIt may serve as a distraction, but you don’t have much time. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4974
    old "“I, too, {i}can see the value of a kind gesture{/i}.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4974
    old "“Huh, are we {i}conspiring{/i}?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4974
    old "“First of all, the stuff I’m asking for isn’t yours.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:4974
    old "“I’m honored to be of aid.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5017
    old "“When do we start?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5017
    old "“Are there not enough guards for such a task?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5017
    old "“What threats should I expect?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5017
    old "“Very well. I’ll speak to the guards in the morning.”"
