    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5057
    old "A gentle smile - in her eyes only. “I know where the things you seek are, en ne just the wand. I’m eva willing to give them back.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5072
    old "After you mention that you were meant to ask for work, you’re taken beyond the gate and led toward the forest garden. The field workers observe you for a bit, and one even runs closer, pretending they have to ask a guard if they’re still on for a beer in the evening, but a swift lie gets rid of them quickly - “The warden’s about to examine some weird trails.” \n\nYour walk ends where the garden gets slightly darker, between three crabapple trees. Two of them are heavy with fruit, but one is already earning its first autumn leaves. It’s past its prime - its destiny of being cut into timber is fast approaching. \n\nYou’re told to wait for {i}the druid{/i} to join you. And to avoid drawing too much attention. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5072
    old "“Because of the people, or the beasts?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5072
    old "“I can handle myself.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5072
    old "“What {i}if{/i} someone starts asking questions?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5094
    old "I stay in the shadows."
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5100
    old "The hooded, cloaked figure chose dark green, matching the local foliage quite well, but considering the size of everyone in the village, not many of the locals would be able to hide in plain sight. Once they get closer, you recognize them by their physique alone - it’s the same large, broad-shouldered man who usually guards the entrance to the square of druids, though this time he remembered about his sandals. \n\n“Ready?” He rushes you without a greeting. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5100
    old "“Ready.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5100
    old "“What are we doing, exactly?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5112
    old "[custom1] \n\nYou stick to the beaten trails. The only songs and calls you hear are coming from birds and monkeys. \n\n“I gave the head forager clear instructions, we ought to find nae one in our way. But be on the lookout - you’re meant to distract them, away from me.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5112
    old "“You kind of draw attention to yourself.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5120
    old "He maintains his pace. The annoyance in his voice seems to be aimed more at the situation in general, than at you. “The spells we learn are aimed at wounds, soil, plants, hearts,” he explains. “Combat, ne so much. I, however, used to be a guard.” He straightens his arm, and his club shows up in his hand, still strapped to his wrist. “If a bearfolk were to jump at you, I’d at least try to hit its head.” \n\nThe further north you get, the thicker the bushes. The paths get even narrower, and you start having to push the bushes aside. \n\n“Who knows what lurks ahead. Better stay quiet.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5120
    old "“Won’t you tell me anything about this garden?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5120
    old "“What makes you so sure the guards are not speaking with {color=#f6d6bd}Thais{/color} right now?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5120
    old "“A guard, huh? What made you join {color=#f6d6bd}Elpis{/color}?”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5128
    old "He swings his club, but his voice remains calm, if not disinterested. “It used to be more wild, when I was a pup. With poisonous mushrooms, sour fruit, nests of saurians en runners. Now, ‘tis more of a tamed yard,” he says reluctantly, “more useful to us than to the beast tribes of old. We eva have plants of the south, like say,” he looks around, “the elderberry here,” he points at a shrub bearing clusters of black fruit coming out of pink finger-like stems. “Our mayor bought the saplings, en they rooted. For better or worse.” \n\nHe picks up the pace. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5128
    old "I guess no more talking."
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5137
    old "“They’re ne {i}the guards{/i},” his tone gets sharper than usual. “They’re our neighbors. Friends. Spouses. Children. Siblings. They care for us, en we for them. We’ll return the favor when the right time comes.” \n\nHe picks up the pace. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5137
    old "I guess I hit a nerve."
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5146
    old "It takes him a good few breaths to respond. “I did ne {i}join{/i} {color=#f6d6bd}Elpis{/color}. I was {i}inspired{/i} by her father. He left. She remains - en her knowledge is undeniable.” \n\nHe takes longer strides. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5146
    old "I speed up as well."
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5155
    old "He lets out a sigh of relief and looks around. His eyes follow the loud animals living on the tree crowns. "
