    old "She’s not hiding her presence, crooning even after she notices you - though a surprised pause occurs first. She sends you a smile, and you’re sure the two of you have exchanged a glance or two during your stay, back in the village. \n\nHer appearance may not be too memorable - humble height and stature, at least for the standards of her tribe, brown, simply tied hair, gambeson in the color of natural linen, an axe by her side - but what draws your attention is the tiny, green-and-creamish monkey clinging to her arm, every now and them moving from one shoulder to another or even sitting on the top of her head. It looks around curiously and occasionally lets out a screech, as if noticing something worth acknowledging. \n\nYou are also greeted with one of these screams. It has brown eyes, just like its owner. The woman comes closer, so you walk a bit down the trail, away from the withered patch. You meet by a large boulder, next to a pile of gathered twigs. "
