    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5827
    old "Before you reach the gate, you find three washwomen who are walking down the path, chatting loudly. The wet hair on their arms and legs shines, contrasting the mud on their feet. Some of them wear soaked shirts; all have their heads wrapped in kerchiefs. You know from the city how hard, and sometimes dangerous, their job can get - you glance over their laundry bats, baskets filled with clothes, and buckets of urine. \n\nOnce they notice you, one of them puts her things next to a fence, and tells the others to go ahead without her. Her companions giggle, but loyally leave the two of you alone. \n\n“I was so hoping to speak with a vagr... A traveler,” she starts and looks away. Whenever she speaks, she’s both very direct and distracted, struggling to explain her plans. After a brief conversation, you try to sum it all up. “So you seek a man who’d agree to take part in the marriage rites of your druids,” she nods energetically, but then freezes. She’s tanned from work, but her face is young and smooth, and since her hair is hidden, her bright hazel eyes keep drawing your attention. \n\n“Ne just {i}any{/i} man,” she interrupts you angrily. “Someone who stays in the sun and works hard, for us en our kids!” You ask if she has any children already, and after another minute of her awkward explanations you take a guess that she doesn’t. \n\nYou ask if it would make a difference for her to move to a different village. “We live good lives here, safe en plentiful. I’d rather stay, but I could leave with a safe convoy.” "
    new ""

