    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5895
    old "She shouts and jumps toward you, throwing her arms around your neck. “En I had such an awful day! Thank you!” With tears in her eyes, she steps away, though your clothes and cheek are already covered with droplets of water. \n\n“Of course, naething is said for sure!” Her calm words are betrayed by her excited tone. “I’ll ask my {color=#f6d6bd}uncle Ak{/color}, I mean {color=#f6d6bd}Akakios{/color}, to ne be so rabid when he swaps dragon bones with you!” \n\nAfter another few minutes of her insisting that you {i}have to{/i} come to the wedding, if it occurs, but nothing for sure, but you must promise, but who knows, but you {i}must{/i} be there - you leave her with her friends. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:5916
    old "He doesn’t notice your approach until you sit down opposite him. He raises his chin - one of his eyes is brown, while the other is white from blindness. Having only one ear, a broken nose, and a constantly open mouth, he looks like a soul at the end of a painful journey, but his voice is more amused than tired. \n\n“En who fell here, on ma very own plate? You’re the, you know, the kid of...” He pauses, leaning a bit forward. “Nah, I have ne seen you before. You come to buy me a strong mug?” \n\nYou need a few breaths to get through his thick accent, additionally distorted by his lack of teeth. "
