    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:6063
    old "He raises his head just enough to take another sip of ale. “The storm shoved us into the rocks, but we knew the stories, so we reached the port en its tunnel. Building the raft took us two days, all the logs en vines we had to cut... There were five of us at first. Two lived long enough to hit the sea again, en only I reached the coast. Ma wife bled out in ma arms. The beasts took us one by one,” his voice gets even weaker, “nae spirit would hear our pleas in that cursed land.” \n\nYou think about a response while {color=#f6d6bd}the sailor{/color} lowers his head again and closes his eyes - the dead one remains half-open. “Want ma advice?” He can’t see your nod. “The moon en stars can ne reach the island. You want to see anything, take lights with you. Now, ask me naething more.” "
