    # game/areas/howlersdell3othernpcs.rpy:6091
    old "You ask an archeress if she could point you to the trapper, and she directs you beyond the walls, to the edge of the northern pasturage. There, next to the creek, a lone wanderer examines simple box traps. They’re placed every few steps, and, judging by the man’s empty sack, so far all of them have turned out to be empty. \n\nHearing your steps, the man sends you a glance, but soon returns to his task. In the city, he’d barely be seen as an adult - his facial hair is sparse and light, and he’s shorter and slimmer than most women in his tribe. His elegant, dark blue tunic suits his tanned skin, and the long dagger he’s carrying has a carved handle. \n\nHe’s crouching, looking toward the other bank and playing with blades of grass. "
