    old "“Ye must understand. Yer a roadster, people ask ye for help, they don’t think ye’ll steal from them when they’re in their beds,” he pats his bag. “It’s not the same when yer a drifter. They don’t ask me to stay, to marry their kids, or to help them with the harvest, they just ask if I {i}plan to pay{/i} for the room, or buy stuff.” \n\nYou talk for quite some time, though it’s difficult to uncover the details hidden in his tale. \n\nHe claims he and his pack bird came here by boat, about which he refuses to speak. He landed just next to {color=#f6d6bd}Gale Rocks{/color}, a large fishing village near the northern shore. The people there were irritable and unwilling to idly chat with him, but “opened their mouths” after he helped them at the smokehouse. On sunny days, the locals hunt on the shore, and when it gets dark, they hide behind the walls, gutting the fish. \n\n“And when the weather goes to shit, they boil water for salt and put fish in it, then hop to the barrels, though I don’t know, they don’t have many trees around. Then they sell the meat to the villages and... And, ye know. Places.” He clears his throat. “For crops.” "
