    old "“I was told to stay away from {color=#f6d6bd}White Marshes{/color}, though no shell told me why. I joined a group of fish traders who were going to {color=#f6d6bd}Old Págos{/color} and its monastery. B’I hate that place, bah, everyone does,” he shrugs. “I traded there for a bit, the villagers are cold, they spend days praying and talking on and on about their {i}duty{/i}, and are gray like an ashworm. So I left at dawn, me and my bird, and wasn’t that a mistake!” \n\nHe was attacked by a short bear-like creature. He tried to run away, but following his bird was a bad idea. He fell over in the thicket, so the monster had time to get to him. “I hit it with a bolt, wasn’t enough. I kick it, so it bites my legs, tears my flesh away. I almost dozed off from the pain, ba’can ye believe it? That lazy bird came back and charged at it with its beak!” His dagger was enough to get through the surprised animal’s belly. It ran away. "
